<br>
I need to know how to pull the Wraith of the Shissar…<br>
<br>
When he spawns, he’ll be in the temple behind the fire wall full of Amygdalin Knights.<br>
<br>
How can I pull him? Is it possible to pull him single? Or does the Temple need to be cleared?<br>
<br>
How many people would it require to do this? (Assuming I need to clear the Temple first.)<br>
<br>
ANY advice you guys have would be MUCH appreciated.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Goji<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maniron>Maniron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 5:29:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7979.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to pull the Wraith of the Shissar?</span><hr size=1> You have to clear temple first.  Nine of us (all 65 with good gear) did it last night for a chanter friend, with a 65 Monk pulling.  We had two chanters and they were the only deaths...be prepared for lots of adds when clearing. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102862&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maniron Warstar -  65 Arch Convoker</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.darkbreednorrath.com"> Dark Breed of Norrath</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1452<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:41:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7979.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to pull the Wraith of the Shissar?</span><hr size=1> Just did this recently <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
61 Mage, 61 Enchanter, 61 Monk, 61 Cleric, 64 Druid, 60 Warrior, 58 Rogue, 57 monk. (mage, monks and rogue all epic'd)<br>
<br>
(1) SW ledge break-in<br>
(2) Clear western part of zone, work your way North<br>
(3) Clear Amys around temple and other mobs in northern part of zone until you can get a shot at Shissar<br>
<br>
I kept finger on the CoH hotkey during pulls, monk would pull them away, FD and CoH, get healed, and pull a bit more, FD, CoH, and repeat until we could split mobs into 1-3 at a time pulls.  Finally, monk called &quot;Inc Shissar&quot;, was a solo pull and went down pretty easy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 4:41:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7979.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to pull the Wraith of the Shissar?</span><hr size=1> I did it!<br>
<br>
Here's how <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
North Wall break.. cleared the area just to the West of the Ring of Fire.<br>
<br>
(Here's where Necros shine in pulling heheh)<br>
<br>
I ran through the Ring of Fire, threw up a DA spell and ran along the West side of the temple shouting horrible things about squid faced freaks and saw a dozen or so harm touches bounce harmlessly off my DA. Then I turned due West and ran out of the ring (I ate 3 harm touches after DA wore off and a few rounds of melee.)<br>
<br>
I ran about 100 yards outside the ring and feigned. I hit F9 to switch to external view and there was a line of mobs leading all the way back to the ring of fire!<br>
<br>
But on top of me, was THE SHISSAR.<br>
<br>
All the other mobs started to walk back, but the Shissar was a corpse camping pig… Unfortunately, before I could type “Don’t come tag yet!” our Mage ran up and aggroed the whole train.<br>
<br>
He ran them around for a little but, but the Shissar stayed on top of me. I stood up and ran him to the zone wall and had our Monk come tag him off me.<br>
<br>
Dead Shissar! Didn’t have to fight ONE temple mob. (/Mourn Mage)<br>
<br>
I'm now certain I can single pull the Shissar from a full temple spawn again.<br>
